External knowledge: 
- Patients with multiple medical records are those who have visited the healthcare provider more than once;
- The most recent prediction is the one made closest to the current date;
- Accuracy of predictions refers to whether the predicted diabetes status matches the actual status recorded in the patient's most recent medical record.

