- Glucose concentration, measured in millimoles per liter (mmol/L) or milligrams per deciliter (mg/dL), is a key indicator of blood sugar levels.

- Health interventions refer to actions taken to improve patients' health, such as diet changes or medication; 
- Outcomes represent the results of these interventions, which can be improved, no change, or other categories; 
